Germany’s FDP Criticizes ECB for Buying Bonds, Handelsblatt Says

-- B y   R a g n h i l d   K j e t l a n d
-- 
2011-08-08T17:46:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-08/germany-s-fdp-criticizes-ecb-for-buying-bonds-handelsblatt-says.html
Germany’s Free Democratic Party
lawmaker  Frank Schaeffler  said the  European Central Bank  is
putting the savings of millions of citizens on the line by
buying Italian and Spanish bonds today,  Handelsblatt  reported,
citing an interview.  Schaeffler, who is the parliamentary finance spokesman for
Chancellor Angela Merkel’s coalition partner FDP, said the ECB
has become the “largest bad bank in the world next to the U.S.
Federal Reserve,” according to the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story: Ragnhild Kjetland in
Frankfurt at   rkjetland@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kenneth Wong in Berlin at 
 kwong11@bloomberg.net  